de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.api

Class Uby

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.lmf.api.Uby
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    UbyQuickAPI, UbyStatistics

    public class Uby
extends java.lang.Object
    Uby class represents the main entrance point to the UBY API. It holds methods for searching of different UBY-LMF elements in a database containing a LexicalResource.

    Methods of this class return fully initialized UBY-LMF class instances. For performance reasons, you also may want to use UbyQuickAPI.

    Author:
    Judith Eckle-Kohler, Michael Matuschek, Tri-Duc Nghiem, Silvana Hartmann, Zijad Maksuti

      • getLexicalEntries

        public java.util.List<LexicalEntry> getLexicalEntries(java.lang.String word,
                                             EPartOfSpeech pos,
                                             Lexicon lexicon)
        Fetches a List of LexicalEntry instances which written representation is the specified word. Optionally lexical entries can be filtered by part-of-speech and a Lexicon.
        Parameters:
        word - the written representation of the lexical entries to be fetched
        pos - the part-of-speech of the lexical entries to be fetched. Set to null in order to skip part-of-speech filtering and fetch all lexical entries matching other constraints, regardless of their part-of-speech.
        lexicon - If not null, filters lexical entries by the specified lexicon. Note that the Lexicon instance has to be obtained beforehand.
        Returns:
        A list of lexical entries matching the specified criteria. If no lexical entry matches the specified criteria, this method returns an empty list.
        See Also:
        EPartOfSpeech, LexicalEntry.getLemma()

                                                 java.lang.String externalRef)
        Returns the Sense instance contained in the database accessed by this Uby instance. The returned senses are filtered by the given name of the external system and external reference.
        Parameters:
        externalSys - the String representing the name of external system, such as "VerbNet" or "WordNet".
        externalRef - the reference string from external system, such as:
      • with verbnet: "retire_withdraw-82-3"
      • with wordnet: "bow_out%2:41:01::"
        • Returns:
        a List of all senses filtered by the given arguments or an empty list if if one of the given arguments is null or the accessed database does not contain any senses matching both constraints

      • areSensesAxes

        public boolean areSensesAxes(Sense sense1,
                    Sense sense2)
        Consumes two Sense instances and returns true if and only if the consumed instances are aligned by a SenseAxis instance.

        Parameters:
        sense1 - the sense to be checked for alignment with sense2
        sense2 - the sense to be checked for alignment with sense1
        Returns:
        true if and only if sense1 has an alignment to sense2 by a sense axis instance so that sense1 is the first sense of a sense axis and sense2 the second.
        This method returns false if one of the consumed senses is null.
        See Also:
        SenseAxis.getSenseOne(), SenseAxis.getSenseTwo()

      • getSensesAxis

        @Deprecated
public java.util.List<SenseAxis> getSensesAxis(java.util.List<Sense> listSense)
        Deprecated. use UbyQuickAPI.lightSenseAxes(List) instead
        Consumes a List of Sense instances and returns a List of all SenseAxis instances aligning senses from the consumed list. In particular, every returned sense axis aligns two senses from the consumed list.

        listSense - A list of senses for which the sense alignments should be returned.

      • wordNetSenses

        public java.util.List<Sense> wordNetSenses(java.lang.String partOfSpeech,
                                  java.lang.String offset)
                                    throws UbyInvalidArgumentException
        Consumes a synset offset (in WordNet terminology) and a part-of-speech. Returns a List of all Sense instances which are derived from the WordNets synset, identified by the consumed arguments.
        Parameters:
        partOfSpeech - a string describing part of speech of the senses to be returned.

        Valid values are:

      • "noun"
      • "verb"
      • "adverb"
      • "adjective"
        • offset - string representation of the WordNets synset offset i.e. "14469014"
        Returns:
        senses derived from the WordNets synset, described by the consumed arguments

        This method returns an empty list if the database accessed by this Uby instance does not contain the specified sense.

        Throws:
        UbyInvalidArgumentException - if the specified part of speech is not valid or one of consumed arguments is null
        Since:
        0.2.0

      • wordNetSense

        public Sense wordNetSense(java.lang.String partOfSpeech,
                 java.lang.String senseKey)
                   throws UbyInvalidArgumentException
        Consumes a sense key (in WordNet terminology) and a part-of-speech. Returns a Sense instance which is derived from the WordNets sense, identified by the consumed arguments.
        Parameters:
        partOfSpeech - a string describing part of speech of the sense to be returned.

        Valid values are:

      • "noun"
      • "verb"
      • "adverb"
      • "adjective"
        • senseKey - string representation of the WordNets identifier of a sense i.e. "enter%2:33:00::"
        Returns:
        UBY-LMF sense derived from the WordNets word, described by the consumed arguments

        This method returns null if the database accessed by this Uby instance does not contain the specified sense.

        Throws:
        UbyInvalidArgumentException - if the specified part of speech is not valid or one of the consumed arguments is null
        Since:
        0.2.0

      • getSensesByOWSynTransId

        public java.util.List<Sense> getSensesByOWSynTransId(java.lang.String synTransId)
        Consumes an identifier of a SynTrans (in OmegaWiki terminology) and returns a List of all Sense instances derived from the specified SynTrans.
        A SynTrans in OmegaWiki corresponds to a sense in WordNet. As OmegaWikis senses are not ordered by frequency, the otherwise unused index field is used to store the original SynTransId, hence making the additional join with MonolingualExternalRef unnecessary.
        Parameters:
        synTransId - a String representation of a unique identifier of OmegaWikis SynTrans
        Returns:
        list of all senses derived from specified OmegaWikis SynTrans.
        This method returns an empty list if a SynTrans with specified identifier does not exist or the database accessed by this Uby instance does not contain a OmegaWiki Lexicon.
